text: Hazi Aslanov is a Baku Metro station. It was opened on 10 December 2002. It is named after the Azerbaijani-Soviet major general, Hazi Aslanov. ==Related pages== *List of Baku metro stations ==References== Category:Baku Metro stations Category:2002 establishments in Asia Category:2002 establishments in Europe
title: Hazi Aslanov (Baku Metro)
